.SH "Fragment Copy Button"
.PP
Shows a copy button when the user hovers over a code fragment:

.PP

.PP

.PP
.SS "Installation"
.IP "1." 4
Add the required resources in your \fRDoxyfile\fP:
.IP "  \(bu" 4
\fBHTML_EXTRA_FILES:\fP \fRdoxygen-awesome-fragment-copy-button\&.js\fP
.IP "  \(bu" 4
\fBHTML_COPY_CLIPBOARD:\fP \fRNO\fP required with Doxygen >= 1\&.10\&.0
.PP

.IP "2." 4
In the \fRheader\&.html\fP template, include \fRdoxygen-awesome-fragment-copy-button\&.js\fP at the end of the \fR<head>\fP and then initialize it: 
.PP
.nf
<html>
    <head>
        <!\-\- \&.\&.\&. other metadata & script includes \&.\&.\&. \-\->
        <script type="text/javascript" src="$relpath^doxygen\-awesome\-fragment\-copy\-button\&.js"></script>
        <script type="text/javascript">
            DoxygenAwesomeFragmentCopyButton\&.init()
        </script>
    </head>
    <body>

.fi
.PP

.PP
.SS "Customizing"
The tooltip of the button can be changed: 
.PP
.nf
DoxygenAwesomeFragmentCopyButton\&.title = "In die Zwischenablage kopieren"

.fi
.PP

.PP
The icon can be changed\&. It must be an SVG: 
.PP
.nf
DoxygenAwesomeFragmentCopyButton\&.copyIcon = `<svg \&.\&.\&.>`
DoxygenAwesomeFragmentCopyButton\&.successIcon = `<svg \&.\&.\&.>`

.fi
.PP

.PP
All customizations must be applied before calling \fRDoxygenAwesomeDarkModeToggle\&.init()\fP!
.SH "Paragraph Linking"
.PP
Provides a button that appears on hover behind every headline, allowing easy creation of a permanent link to the headline:

.PP

.PP

.PP

.PP
Works for all headlines and for many documentation section titles\&.
.SS "Installation"
.IP "1." 4
Add the required resources in your \fRDoxyfile\fP:
.IP "  \(bu" 4
\fBHTML_EXTRA_FILES:\fP \fRdoxygen-awesome-paragraph-link\&.js\fP
.PP

.IP "2." 4
In the \fRheader\&.html\fP template, include \fRdoxygen-awesome-paragraph-link\&.js\fP at the end of the \fR<head>\fP and then initialize it: 
.PP
.nf
<html>
    <head>
        <!\-\- \&.\&.\&. other metadata & script includes \&.\&.\&. \-\->
        <script type="text/javascript" src="$relpath^doxygen\-awesome\-paragraph\-link\&.js"></script>
        <script type="text/javascript">
            DoxygenAwesomeParagraphLink\&.init()
        </script>
    </head>
    <body>

.fi
.PP

.PP
.SS "Customizing"
The button tooltip can be changed:

.PP
.PP
.nf
DoxygenAwesomeParagraphLink\&.title = "Abschnitt verknüpfen"
.fi
.PP

.PP
The icon of the button can be changed\&. Both plain characters and SVG icons are supported:

.PP
.PP
.nf
DoxygenAwesomeParagraphLink\&.icon = "¶"
.fi
.PP

.PP
All customizations must be applied before calling \fRDoxygenAwesomeParagraphLink\&.init()\fP!
.SH "Interactive TOC"
.PP
On large screens, the Table of Contents (TOC) is anchored at the top right of the page\&. This extension visualizes the reading progress by dynamically highlighting the currently active section\&.

.PP
On small screens, the extension hides the TOC by default\&. The user can open it manually when needed:

.PP
  
.SS "Installation"
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
Starting from Doxygen Version 1\&.14\&.0, you have to specify \fRPAGE_OUTLINE_PANEL=NO\fP in your Doxyfile to use this extension\&.
.RE
.PP
.IP "1." 4
Add the required resources in your \fRDoxyfile\fP:
.IP "  \(bu" 4
\fBHTML_EXTRA_FILES:\fP \fRdoxygen-awesome-interactive-toc\&.js\fP
.PP

.IP "2." 4
In the \fRheader\&.html\fP template, include \fRdoxygen-awesome-interactive-toc\&.js\fP at the end of the \fR<head>\fP and then initialize it: 
.PP
.nf
<html>
    <head>
        <!\-\- \&.\&.\&. other metadata & script includes \&.\&.\&. \-\->
        <script type="text/javascript" src="$relpath^doxygen\-awesome\-interactive\-toc\&.js"></script>
        <script type="text/javascript">
            DoxygenAwesomeInteractiveToc\&.init()
        </script>
    </head>
    <body>

.fi
.PP

.PP
.SS "Customizing"
The offset for when a headline is considered active can be changed\&. A smaller value means that the headline of the section must be closer to the top of the viewport before it is highlighted in the TOC:

.PP
.PP
.nf
DoxygenAwesomeInteractiveToc\&.topOffset = 45
.fi
.PP

.PP
Hiding the TOC on small screens can be disabled\&. It is still interactive and can be hidden by the user but will now be open by default:

.PP
.PP
.nf
DoxygenAwesomeInteractiveToc\&.hideMobileMenu = false
.fi
.PP
.SH "Tabs"
.PP
This extension allows to arrange list content in tabs:

.PP

.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBTab 1\fP This is the content of tab 1
.IP "\(bu" 2
\fBTab 2\fP This is the content of tab 2
.IP "  1." 6
it has a list
.IP "  2." 6
with multiple items
.PP

.PP

.PP
.SS "Installation"
.IP "1." 4
Add the required resources in your \fRDoxyfile\fP:
.IP "  \(bu" 4
\fBHTML_EXTRA_FILES:\fP \fRdoxygen-awesome-tabs\&.js\fP
.PP

.IP "2." 4
In the \fRheader\&.html\fP template, include \fRdoxygen-awesome-tabs\&.js\fP at the end of the \fR<head>\fP and then initialize it: 
.PP
.nf
<html>
    <head>
        <!\-\- \&.\&.\&. other metadata & script includes \&.\&.\&. \-\->
        <script type="text/javascript" src="$relpath^doxygen\-awesome\-tabs\&.js"></script>
        <script type="text/javascript">
            DoxygenAwesomeTabs\&.init()
        </script>
    </head>
    <body>

.fi
.PP

.PP
.SS "Usage"
Each list that is supposed to be displayed as tabs must be wrapped with the \fRtabbed\fP CSS class\&. Each item in the list must start with an element that has the class \fRtab-title\fP\&. It will then be used as the tab title\&.

.PP
.PP
.nf
<div class="tabbed">

\- <b class="tab\-title">Tab 1</b> This is the content of tab 1
\- <b class="tab\-title">Tab 2</b> This is the content of tab 2

</div>
.fi
.PP
.SH "Page Navigation"
.PP
To allow users to easily navigate from one document to another, "Next" and "Previous" buttons can be added at the end of a Markdown document\&.
.SS "Installation"
The feature is included in the default \fRdoxygen-awesome\&.css\fP\&. No additional stylesheets or scripts need to be added\&.
.SS "Usage"
The following conditions must be met for the feature to work properly:

.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
The navigation must be inside a Markdown table with 1-2 columns\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
The alignment of the column defines the alignment of the arrow on the navigation button\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
The table must be wrapped inside a \fR<div>\fP with the class \fRsection_buttons\fP\&.
.PP

.PP

.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Code 
.PP
.nf
<div class="section_buttons">

| Previous          |                              Next |
|:\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-|\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-:|
| [Home](README\&.md) | [Customization](customization\&.md) |

</div>

.fi
.PP

.IP "\(bu" 2
Result  Previous  Next  \fBHome\fP  \fBCustomization\fP  
.PP

.PP

.PP

